-600 rounded-full px-3 py-1","children":"metadata"}],["$","span","automation",{"className":"text-xs font-mono bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 rounded-full px-3 py-1","children":"automation"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose-goated","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Every song has dozens of metadata fields: title, artist name, composer, publisher, ISRC code, copyright info, royalty splits, release date, and more."}]]}],["$","p","1",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"For independent labels, managing this is a nightmare. Spreadsheets get out of sync. Metadata is incorrect across platforms. Royalty payments are manual and error-prone."}]]}],["$","p","2",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"We built a metadata system for an independent music label with 500+ releases. Here is what actually works."}]]}],["$","h2","3",{"className":"font-serif text-2xl text-dark mt-12 mb-4","children":"The Metadata Problem for Labels"}],["$","h3","4",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"1. Multiple stakeholders, one source of truth"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"A release has the artist, composer, multiple featured artists, producers, engineers, songwriters. Each person might have different info. Your spreadsheet cannot model relationships."}]]}],["$","h3","6",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"2. ISRC codes are critical"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Each track needs an ISRC code for rights management and earnings tracking. ISRC registration is manual and error-prone."}]]}],["$","h3","8",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"3. Royalty splits are complex"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"A song might have:"}]]}],["$","li","10",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Artist gets 50%"}]]}],["$","li","11",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Composer gets 30%"}]]}],["$","li","12",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Publisher gets 20%"}]]}],["$","li","13",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed ml-5 mb-2 list-disc","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"But if the composer is not the artist, the split changes"}]]}],["$","p","14",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Your spreadsheet cannot automate this."}]]}],["$","h3","15",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"4. Distribution requires metadata in specific format"}],["$","p","16",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Spotify, Apple Music, Amazon Music all require different metadata formats, different spellings of artist names, different ISRC formats."}]]}],["$","h3","17",{"className":"font-sans text-lg font-semibold text-dark mt-8 mb-3","children":"5. Discrepancies cost money"}],["$","p","18",{"className":"font-sans text-base text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","span","0",{"children":"Wrong ISRC code means the song is not matched to earnings. Wrong composer name means royalties go to the wrong person. Wrong release date means the song is not distributed to some platf